ce:section.ce:para:
ZnPc-CQDs were synthesized by microwave-assisted preparation from ZnPc in the presence of citric acid (CA) (Scheme 1
                        ). Fig. 1
                        a shows the morphology of ZnPc-CQDs which was characterized by TEM. ZnPc-CQDs were spherical nanoparticles with good dispersion, with Fig.an average diameter of 5 nm, which was well agree with the DLS analysis (5.2 ± 1.2 nm) (Fig. 1b). As shown in Fig. 1c, the FT-IR spectrum of ZnPc-CQDs showed characteristic peaks at 1740 and 1430 cm−1, which were attributed to the CO stretching vibrations of carboxyl groups. Moreover, the signals at 1609 cm−1 assigning to CC vibrated from phenyl group was not observed, which indicated that the surface of the synthesized ZnPc-CQDs is covered with carboxyl groups.
